# Mielonka — project knowledge for new Claude sessions

## What this project is

Laravel 11 application that imports raw data from external sources (WHMCS, Gmail, IMAP, MetricsCube) into local PostgreSQL `source_*` tables. A full admin panel manages connections, triggers jobs, and streams live logs. Deployed via Docker Compose on a production server.

## Stack

- **PHP 8.3** / Laravel 11, queue driver: database, session: database, cache: database
- **PostgreSQL** (container `db`, port 5433 external / 5432 internal)
- **Alpine.js** (no build step) for admin UI reactivity
- **Tailwind CSS** loaded from CDN
- Docker Compose: `app` (PHP + FrankenPHP on :8080), `db`, `worker`, `scheduler`

## Source types and importers

| Type | Importer class | Source table | Checkpoint key pattern |
|---|---|---|---|
| `whmcs` | `app/Importers/Whmcs/` (4 classes) | `source_whmcs_*` | `source_system='salesos', importer='whmcs_api', entity='clients'` etc |
| `gmail` | `app/Importers/Gmail/ImportGmailMessages.php` | `source_gmail_messages` | `ImportCheckpointStore` with key `gmail\|messages\|{system}\|{email}\|{query}` |
| `imap` | `app/Importers/Imap/ImportImapMessages.php` | `source_imap_messages` | `ImportCheckpointStore` with key `imap\|messages\|{account}\|{mailbox}` |
| `metricscube` | `app/Importers/Whmcs/ImportMetricsCubeClients.php` | `source_metricscube_client_activities` | standard checkpoint |

## Key architectural patterns

### Checkpointing
`app/Support/ImportCheckpointStore.php` — generic key→JSON store backed by `import_checkpoints` table. Uses `upsert()` with `source_system='checkpoint_store', importer='v1', entity='v1', cursor_type=md5($key)`. Checkpoint key is the full semantic key (system, mailbox, query, etc.).

### Hash-based change detection
Every importer computes a SHA-256 `row_hash` over the sanitised payload JSON. Rows are inserted on first seen, updated only when hash changes, skipped otherwise. This produces insert/update/skip counts in logs.

### Gmail volatile field stripping
Gmail API returns two fields that change on every API call even if message content is unchanged:
- `historyId` — at the top level of the message object → `unset($payloadForHash['historyId'])`
- `attachmentId` — **inside `payload.parts[i].body`** (NOT at top level) → `stripVolatileFields()` is called on `$payloadForHash['payload']` (the nested payload object), not the top-level message

```php
// CORRECT:
if (isset($payloadForHash['payload'])) {
    $payloadForHash['payload'] = $this->stripVolatileFields($payloadForHash['payload']);
}
// WRONG (was a bug — top-level message has no 'body' key):
// $payloadForHash = $this->stripVolatileFields($payloadForHash);
```

Gmail API message structure:
```json
{
  "id": "...", "threadId": "...", "historyId": "...", "internalDate": "...",
  "labelIds": [...], "snippet": "...", "sizeEstimate": ...,
  "payload": {
    "partId": "", "mimeType": "multipart/mixed", "headers": [...],
    "body": {"size": 0},
    "parts": [
      {"mimeType": "text/plain", "body": {"data": "..."}},
      {"mimeType": "application/pdf",  "body": {"attachmentId": "ANGjdJ...", "size": ...}}
    ]
  }
}
```

### Gmail concurrent fetching
`ImportGmailMessages::fetchConcurrently()` uses `Http::pool()` to fetch all messages on a page in parallel. One `messages.list` request → N concurrent `messages.get?format=full` requests.

### Jobs
`app/Jobs/RunConnection.php` — dispatches any connection type. Creates `ConnectionRun` row, buffers log lines to JSONB column every 10 lines or 3 seconds, marks run completed/failed.

`app/Console/Commands/RunScheduledConnections.php` — runs every minute via scheduler container, checks cron expressions, dispatches jobs for due connections (skips if already pending/running).

### IMAP UID search
Uses `imap_search($mbox, 'UID N:999999999', SE_UID)` (NOT `N:*`) to avoid RFC 3501 edge case where `*` equals current max UID and some servers return already-seen messages.

## Admin panel

**Routes prefix:** `/admin` (auth middleware: `admin.auth`)
**Controller:** `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/ConnectionController.php`
**Views:** `resources/views/admin/`

### Key admin endpoints

| Method | Route | Action |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/admin/connections` | index (connections list) |
| POST | `/admin/connections/{id}/run` | trigger run (returns `{run_id, already_active}`) |
| GET | `/admin/connections/runs/{run}/logs` | poll logs (returns `{log_lines, status}`) |
| GET | `/admin/connections/runs/{run}/status` | poll status only |
| GET | `/admin/connections/{id}/runs` | run history (last 50) |
| POST | `/admin/connections/{id}/stop` | cancel run |
| POST | `/admin/connections/{id}/duplicate` | duplicate connection |
| POST | `/admin/connections/kill-all` | cancel all active runs |

### UI (Alpine.js patterns)
- `adminPanel()` — main component on connections index: manages modal, run/stop/delete/kill-all
- `connRow(connId, runId, initialStatus)` — per-row component: polls status every 4s when active; listens for `run-started-event` on `window` to update badge reactively when `triggerRun` starts a new run
- `connectSSE(runId)` — polls `/runs/{runId}/logs` every 2s; reloads page 2s after run completes/fails; interval survives modal close (so page reloads even if user closes the popup)
- `viewLogs()` / `selectRun()` — both start `connectSSE` if fetched status is pending/running
- Double-click guard in `triggerRun`: `_launching` flag; server-side dedup returns existing run ID if already active

### Google OAuth flow
`app/Http/Controllers/GoogleOAuthController.php`
- `GET /google/auth/{system}?email=` → redirects to Google consent page
- `GET /google/callback/{system}` → exchanges code, stores encrypted refresh_token in `oauth_google_tokens`
- `app/Support/GoogleOAuthConfig.php` — reads per-connection OAuth credentials from DB
- Token stored: `oauth_google_tokens(system, subject_email, refresh_token[encrypted], updated_at)`

## Database

### Important migrations
- `2026_02_22_999999_reset_pgsql_sequences.php` — fixes PostgreSQL sequences out of sync after SQLite→PostgreSQL migration. Uses a PL/pgSQL DO block to `setval(seq, MAX(id))` for every table that has an `id` column (safely skips tables without `id` like `password_reset_tokens`).
- `2026_02_23_000001_create_connections_table.php` — `connections` table
- `2026_02_23_000002_create_connection_runs_table.php` — `connection_runs` table

### Credentials storage
All connection credentials (API keys, passwords, OAuth secrets) are stored as JSONB in `connections.settings`. NOT in `.env`. The job (`RunConnection`) reads settings and injects them into the process environment so importers pick them up via `env()` / config helpers.

